## Relative Paths

---

Relative paths are filepaths written in relation to the file making the reference.

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" />
```

Here, saying `css/style.css` means

> "go into the `css` folder, and get the `style.css` file"

---

There are two important things to know:

- `.` (single dot) refers to the **current folder**
- `..` (double dot) refers to the **parent folder**

So I can say `./css/style.css` to mean

> "from the **current folder**, go into the `css` folder, and get the `style.css` file"

Or `../images/daffodils.jpg` means

> "go into my **parent folder**, then go into the `images` folder, and get the `daffodils.jpg` file"

