## Absolute Paths: HTTPS/HTTP

---

When referring to external resources,
we use absolute paths.

```html
<a href="https://google.com/">Google</a>
```

They start with `https://` or `http://`.

No matter which webpage a user is on,
the above link will take them to https://google.com/.

### HTTPS

Use `https://` wherever possible.
HTTPS is the **secure** version of HTTP.
It protects users by encoding the information they send,
and checks for server certificates that they're on the right website.

