## Absolute Paths: Starting with `/`

---

class: grid-2 grid-no-margins

.grid-column-span-2[
Starting a path with `/` takes us to the **root directory** of the current website.

```html
<a href="/index.html">Homepage</a>
```
]

.group[
In this example, we might be at

- `mywebsite.com/about/index.html`
- `mywebsite.com/pages/01-my-first-page.html`.
- `mywebsite.com/index.html`

The link above would take users to `mywebsite.com/index.html`.
]

.group[
However, if the link above was found on the page at

- `otherwebsite.com/blog/september/01.html`
- `otherwebsite.com/about/our-staff/bob.html`
- `otherwebsite.com/index.html`

The link would take users to `otherwebsite.com/index.html`.
]

.grid-column-span-2[
It's best to avoid using links starting with `/`, and use relative paths instead.
]

