## Using Paths

Using relative paths lets us organise our projects logically.

Front-End Web Developers (like you!) will generally keep all
files in folders with descriptive names, for example

- images in an `images` folder
- all CSS in a `styles` folder
- all JavaScript in a `scripts` folder

This may mean that, from our `styles/main.css` CSS file,
we have to use relative paths to reference background images.

```css
article {
  background-image: url(../images/stars.png);
}
```

Depending on our site structure, we may have a webpage at
`about/index.html`,
which references our stylesheet like so:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles/main.css" />
```

Remember: the relative path is relative to the **file making the reference**.

